author: Manhunt Under Way After Convicted Killer Mistakenly Set Free in Louisiana
title: Vinci beats Kvitova to advance at Wuhan Open
text:
Vinci beats Kvitova to advance at Wuhan Open Associated Press 15 hrs ago WUHAN, China (AP) Roberta Vinci advanced to the quarterfinals of the Wuhan Open by beating defending champion Petra Kvitova 7-6 (3), 6-2 on Wednesday.
AdChoices The 15th-seeded Italian saved five of seven break points.
''Against Petra it's always tough to play,'' Vinci said. ''She's an incredible player, she won last year here. But I played a really good match. She played so well the first few games so I tried not to think about this and focus.''
Also, Venus Williams beat Carla Suarez Navarro of Spain 6-3, 6-4. A day after earning her 700th victory, Williams hit five aces and saved three of four break points.
Williams, a seven-time major champion, improved to 3-3 against Navarro and will next face either top-seeded Simona Halep or Johanna Konta.
Also, fifth-seeded Garbine Muguruza of Spain rallied to beat ninth-seeded Ana Ivanovic of Serbia 4-6, 6-1, 6-0. Muguruza will face Anna Karolina Schmiedlova of Slovakia in the quarterfinals. Schmiedlova beat Kristina Mladenovic of France 6-4, 6-2.
